title: Population of Saba ( Caribbean Netherlands ) 2011 to 2019
summary: This line chart has an x axis representing Year and a y axis representing Number of people, with a total of 9 data points. The chart has 4 significant trends.
The longest trend is extremely positive which exists from 2018 to 2015.
Additionally, the next significant trend is moderately negative which exists from 2015 to 2013.
Differently, the next significant trend is extremely positive which exists from 2013 to 2011.
In a similar manner, the next significant trend is slightly negative which exists from 2019 to 2018.
gold: Between 2011 and 2019 , the population of the Caribbean island Saba increased slightly . Saba , one of the three special municipalities of the Netherlands , counted roughly 1,900 inhabitants in 2019 . Population peaked in 2018 , at approximately 2,150 .
